Germany's New Military Ship Delayed Again
According to local media, the last frigate of the German Navy should have been commissioned in 2014 to replace the old military ships of the times of the cold war, but there will not be at least until next year due to faulty systems and a surge in costs.
The Rhineland-Palatinate commission, the flagship of the new Baden-W<0xC3><0xBC>rttemberg-class frigates, was delayed until the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit citing a military spokesman.
