The problems involving the new frigates become of particular importance in the light of recent alarms regarding the reduction of German naval power.
Earlier this year, Hans-Peter Bartels, Parliamentary Commissioner for the Armed Forces, admitted that the Navy actually "lacks ships that can be used".
The official said the issue has worsened significantly over time, as the old unarmed ships have not been replaced by new ships.
