Foreign buyers will be subject to higher stamp duty for the purchase of property in the UK
Foreign buyers will be subject to higher stamp duties for the purchase of property in the UK and the additional cash flow will be used to help the homeless, according to new plans by Labour.
The maneuver will neutralize Corbyn’s successful initiative to attract young voters.
The increase in stamp duty will be applied to taxpayers who do not pay taxes in the UK
The Ministry of the Treasury plans to raise up to <0xC2><0xA3>120 million a year to help the homeless
