The new policy comes just weeks after Boris Johnson called for a cut in the stamp duty to help younger people buy their first home.
He accused big construction companies of keeping real estate prices high by grabbing land without using it and encouraged Prime Minister May to give up affordable housing quotas to fix Britain’s “real estate woes.”
Mr Corbyn has announced a number of proposals for reform of the housing market, including checks on rents and the elimination of unwarranted evictions.
