"Today the situation on the ground is more stable and secure thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism," he said.
The government continues to recover the areas destroyed by terrorists to restore normalcy.
Now there are all the conditions for the voluntary return of refugees in the country who have had to leave due to terrorism and unilateral economic measures that have affected their daily lives and livelihoods.
According to the United Nations, more than 5.5 million Syrians have left the country since the beginning of the war in 2011.
Another six million people still living in Syria are in need of humanitarian aid.
Al-Moualem said the Syrian regime would gladly accept assistance to rebuild the devastated country.
But he stressed that he will not accept any conditional aid or from those countries that supported the uprising.
Europe wins the Ryder Cup in Paris
The Europa team won the 2018 Ryder Cup by beating the USA team with a final score of 17.5 to 10.5 at Le Golf National outside Paris, France.
The U.S. has lost six consecutive times on European soil and has not won a Ryder Cup in Europe since 1993.
Europe regained the trophy when Danish captain Thomas Bjorn's team reached the 14.5 points they needed to beat the United States.
U.S. champion Phil Mickelson, who fought for most of the tournament, threw his tee shot into the water at the sixteenth hole of par 3 giving victory to Francesco Molinari.
The Italian golfer has distinguished himself in all his rounds by becoming one of only four players to ever score a 5-0-0 since the tournament with the current formula was first played in 1979.
The American Jordan Spieth was defeated with the score of 5&4 by the lower Danish player in the ranking Thorbjorn Olesen of the European team.
The best player in the world, Dustin Johnson, surrendered for 2&1 to Englishman Ian Poulter who may have played his last Ryder Cup.
A veteran of the Ryder Cup, the Spanish Sergio Garcia who has played eight of them, has become the European player who has won the most in the history of the tournament with 25.5 points.
“I usually don’t cry but today I can’t help it.
It's been a rough year.
I am grateful to Thomas for choosing me and believing in me.
I'm so glad I won the cup.
It’s a team win and I’m happy to have made my contribution,” said an excited Garcia after the European win.
